Brown sausage in large skillet on medium-high heat. Meanwhile, drain sweet potatoes, reserving syrup. Slice sweet potatoes. Add water and reserved syrup to skillet; bring to boil. Stir in stuffing mix and sweet potatoes just to moisten. Spoon into 1-1/2-quart casserole; cover. Bake at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.